    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="125"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.811/167.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Reinsch</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 22, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your despatch No. 424 of October 28.</p>
                <p>The engineers’ report indicates Huai River project entirely practicable, but war
                    conditions make impossible now to negotiate loan or contract or obtain advance
                    of funds for immediate use, which Red Cross sincerely regrets. Does China desire
                    continued interest of Red Cross in working out project, which assistance Red
                    Cross will be glad to render as soon as world conditions improve? If so, formal
                    extension of exclusive option to Red Cross desirable. If extension conceded by
                    China, Red Cross would be glad to have it arranged by the American Minister. Two
                    hundred copies of the final report of the Board of Engineers with maps will be
                    forwarded to China within a week.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
